  "chapter": {
    "number": 34,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Elihu Confirms God’s Justice"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Elihu continued:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Hear my words, O wise men;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "give ear to me, O men of learning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the ear tests words",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as the mouth tastes food.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Let us choose for ourselves what is right;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "let us learn together what is good.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For Job has declared, ‘I am righteous,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet God has deprived me of justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Would I lie about my case?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "My wound is incurable,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "though I am without transgression.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What man is like Job,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who drinks up derision like water?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He keeps company with evildoers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and walks with wicked men.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For he has said, ‘It profits a man nothing",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that he should delight in God.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore listen to me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O men of understanding.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Far be it from God to do wrong,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and from the Almighty to act unjustly.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For according to a man’s deeds He repays him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "according to a man’s ways He brings consequences.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Indeed, it is true that God does not act wickedly,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the Almighty does not pervert justice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who gave Him charge over the earth?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Who appointed Him over the whole world?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If He were to set His heart to it",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and withdraw His Spirit and breath,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "all flesh would perish together",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and mankind would return to the dust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you have understanding, hear this;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "listen to my words.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Could one who hates justice govern?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Will you condemn the just and mighty One,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who says to kings, ‘You are worthless!’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to nobles, ‘You are wicked,’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who is not partial to princes",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and does not favor rich over poor?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For they are all the work of His hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They die in an instant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in the middle of the night.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "The people convulse and pass away;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the mighty are removed without human hand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For His eyes are on the ways of a man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He sees his every step.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There is no darkness or deep shadow",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "where the workers of iniquity can hide.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For God need not examine a man further",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or have him approach for judgment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He shatters the mighty without inquiry",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sets up others in their place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, He recognizes their deeds;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He overthrows them in the night and they are crushed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He strikes them for their wickedness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in full view,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "because they turned aside from Him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and had no regard for any of His ways.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They caused the cry of the poor to come before Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He heard the outcry of the afflicted.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But when He remains silent, who can condemn Him?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "When He hides His face, who can see Him?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet He watches over both man and nation,",
            "poem": 1
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "that godless men should not rule",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "or lay snares for the people.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Suppose someone says to God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘I have endured my punishment; I will offend no more.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 32,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Teach me what I cannot see;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "if I have done wrong, I will not do it again.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 33,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Should God repay you on your own terms",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when you have disavowed His?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You must choose, not I;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so tell me what you know.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 34,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Men of understanding will declare to me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the wise men who hear me will say:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 35,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "‘Job speaks without knowledge;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his words lack insight.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 36,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only Job were tried to the utmost",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for answering like a wicked man.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 37,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For he adds rebellion to his sin;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he claps his hands among us",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and multiplies his words against God.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
